               <odd id="aspace_65196bd97a371f6153b7254c7b484034">
                  <head>General note</head>
                  <p>Signatures from a disbound scrapbook containing autograph manuscript letters to Florence and Frederick Marryat from friends, authors, and colleages including Charles Dickens and George Augustus Sala. Some of the letters were written to London publisher Richard Bentley (1794-1871) and were likely acquired by Marryat for their autograph value. Several of the letters have albumen portrait photographs of the letter writer mounted above the letter. The first folder contains two letters from Marryat to her mother. The letters, photographs, and other material remain mounted on their album pages and are in their original order; the fourth folder contains the front and back covers for the album.</p>
               </odd>
            </c>
